title: Letter from Emmanuel Marx to Gretel
creator: Marx, Emmanuel
description: Emmanuel Marx wrote to Gretel Marx from the Ambassador Hotel in Los Angeles, to let her know that a friend of his, Mrs. Moss, would meet her at the dock when her ship arrived in New York in December 1936.  Emmanuel was Gretel's cousin, who was friend with George Raft and ran with a Hollywood crowd (as Gretel recalled it).  He helped her immigrate to Chicago.
subject: Immigration

title: vinegarfactory
creator: Carolyn Faber
description: Introduction to the "Essigfabrik" (vinegar factory) in Flonheim.  Klostereck. Omi pages through a photo album with photos she took of the factory, including her brother Gunther, and other workmen. She explains how it all worked, and how she used to inspect the vats and do quality checks.
subject: Flonheim; Essigfabrik; Vinegar Factory; Klostereck

title: sterfamilyphoto1
creator: Carolyn Faber
description: Omi (Gretel) identifies everyone in a family photo from 1926, when she was about 10 years old, which includes her grandparents, parents, aunts, uncles and cousins from her mother's side (Selma Stern). She identifies who died in the holocaust and some of who survived. She refers to her cousin Rudy Bender as someone who became the Mayor of Hamburg, but what she means is that he was in charge of an Allied sector of Hamburg after WWII.

title: kinofrankintro1
creator: Carolyn Faber
description: This is part of an introduction to Hans "Kino" Frank.  The audio is a 2003 recording of my grandmother telling me about him - this is the first time I heard of him.  She had received an newspaper article from her friend Ilse Diehl, who not only lived in Flonheim, but in the house where my grandmother grew up.  That's another story.  But Ilse had sent this article about Kino Frank, who ran the local cinema and my grandmother thought I would be interested in it.  The article is in German but she's translating it into English for me while also sharing some of her own memories of how she once knew him.    A couple of the shots are from a documentary made in 2001 called Hans Im Gluck, by Sabine Streich. The audio recording is from 2002 and all of the other video footage is from 2006, when I first went to Flonheim as an adult, to meet Kino Frank.
subject: Kino Frank; Gretel Roos; Flonheim; Gunther Marx; Cinema
